      • launch

        public static Command launch(int robotsNumber,
             TrianglePoint from,
             TrianglePoint to)
        Constructs a command to send robot to occupy a vein.
        Parameters:
        robotsNumber - the number of robots to send to the vein. There should be enough robots at the vein from where to send the robots.
        from - the coordinates of the vein to send the robots from. The location shall point to an existing vein owned by the caller.
        to - the coordinates of the vein to send the robots to. The location shall point to a vein owned by the caller.
        Returns:
        the command to send the robots

      • launchWithPath

        public static Command launchWithPath(int robotsNumber,
                     java.util.List<TrianglePoint> path)
        Constructs a command with the number of robots to send, and the coordinates of the vein from and to where the robots should go to.
        Parameters:
        robotsNumber - the number of robots to send to the vein. There should be enough robots at the vein from where to send the robots. vein owned by the caller.
        path - a list of points containing the path to take. The path should at least contain the departure point and the destination.
        Returns:
        the command to send the robots
